result.execSummary:
The defendant Ventura Carranco Villanueva was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Cash Bond of $500.00 previously posted has been applied.  The remaining balance of the fine is to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court by November 25, 2015.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.  Sentence to commence forthwith.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Same repayment provisions apply as noted above for the Fine.

records.addlTxt: 15CM-438 and All Pending Citations Called @ 3:20 PM: Defendant Ventura Carranco Villanueva in court, appearing pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Enrique Soria present as Interpreter.  Oath administered at previous hearing today.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Def requests to speak with the State on resolution.  Off Record for Def to speak directly with the ADA.  Back of Record at 3:27 PM with Court Reporter being present:  Resolution recited by ADA with argued terms on sentencing recommendation.  Def agrees with State's recital.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. 15CM-438 Plea:  GP  15TR-2908 No DL 1:  GP  Court accepts pleas as to both matters and enters JOC.  15TR-2909 and 15TR-2910 both DRI.  15TR-2908 Court Costs imposed - 60 DTP.  Statement by Def:  Yes.  Brief statement by ADA - States Def did contact COC to arrange speedy resolution due to leaving the State soon.  The Court:  Accepts recommendation on resolution.  15CM-438 - credit given for Def's request to resolve matter before leaving the State.  Imposes 20 days WCJ and Court Costs.  Def intends to leave the State on 11/25/2015.  In light of intended date to departure, Court will order 12 days WCJ - GT credit and Huber Privileges granted- 8 days to serve remaining,  Def must report today to commence serving sentence immediately following Court.  Def will be released on 11/25 when he intends to leave.  Fine of $1200 inclusive of costs - bond to be applied.  Hispanic Appeal Rights Given.  Fine to be PIF by 11/25/2015.  DNA sample to be provided today at the WCJ.    Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.
